Selenium IDE:
=============
This is a record and playback tool for creating Selenium test cases. It is a browser plugin 
that allows testers to record their actions on a webpage and generate Selenium code automatically. Selenium IDE 
is a good tool for beginners to learn Selenium as it requires no coding skills.

Selenium Grid:
==============
This component allows you to execute Selenium tests on multiple machines and browsers 
simultaneously. Selenium Grid is used for distributed testing and is a scalable solution for running tests on a 
large number of machines and browsers.

Selenium Remote Control (RC): 
=============================
Selenium RC is the older version of WebDriver. It is a deprecated tool, and 
Selenium WebDriver has replaced it. Selenium RC is used for testing legacy web applications that do not support 
WebDriver.
